'''William Robert Young''' [[Privy Council of Ireland|PC(Ire)]] (c.1856 – 12 September 1933) was an [[Ireland|Irish]] [[linen]] merchant, politician and [[philanthropist]].
Young was born at [[Galgorm Castle]], [[Ballymena]], [[County Antrim]]. He was educated at [[Harrow School]] and then joined the family firm of J. & R. Young of [[Belfast]]. A prominent [[Irish Unionists|Unionist]], he was appointed to the [[Privy Council of Ireland]] in the honours for the opening of the [[Parliament of Northern Ireland]] in July 1921 for his charitable work,<ref>{{London Gazette |issue=32387 |date=12 July 1921 |page=5553}}</ref> entitling him to the style "The Right Honourable".
